#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:2
#, no-c-format
msgid "&turtlescript; Programming Reference"
msgstr "&कच्छपलिपि; प्रोग्रामिंग सन्दर्भ"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:3
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"This is the reference for &kturtle;'s &turtlescript;. In the first section "
"of this chapter have a look at some aspects of the <link linkend=\"grammar"
"\">grammar</link> of &turtlescript; programs. The second section deals "
"exclusively with <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">mathematical "
"operators</link>, <link linkend=\"boolean-operators\">boolean (true/false) "
"operators</link> and <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparison "
"operators</link>. The third section is basically a giant list of all <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">commands</link> explaining them one-by-one. Section "
"four explains how to <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">assign</link> "
"values to <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</link>. "
"Finally we explain how to arrange the execution of commands with <link "
"linkend=\"controlling-execution\">execution controlling statements</link> in "
"section five and how to create you own commands with <link linkend=\"learn"
"\"><userinput>learn</userinput></link> in section six."
msgstr ""
"&amp;kturtle; इत्यस्य &amp;turtlescript; इत्यस्य सन्दर्भः अयं । अस्य अध्यायस्य प्रथमखण्डे "
"केचन पक्षाः अवलोकयन्तु<link linkend=\"grammar\"> व्याकरणम्</link> of &amp;"
"turtlescript; कार्यक्रमाः। द्वितीयः खण्डः अनन्यतया विषयः अस्ति<link linkend="
"\"mathematical-operators\"> गणितीय संचालक</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"boolean-"
"operators\"> boolean (true/false) ऑपरेटर्</link> तथा<link linkend=\"comparing-"
"operators\"> तुलना संचालकाः</link> . तृतीयः खण्डः मूलतः सर्वेषां विशालसूची अस्ति<link "
"linkend=\"commands\"> आदेशाः</link> तान् एकैकं व्याख्याय । चतुर्थे खण्डे कथं करणीयम् इति "
"व्याख्यातम् अस्ति<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> दिश्</link> मूल्यानि "
"to<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चराः</link> . अन्ते वयं "
"व्याख्यास्यामः यत् कथं सह आदेशानां निष्पादनं व्यवस्थापयितुं शक्यते<link linkend="
"\"controlling-execution\"> निष्पादन नियन्त्रक कथनानि</link> पञ्चमे खण्डे तथा च कथं "
"भवता स्वकीयानि आदेशानि निर्मातव्यानि इति<link linkend=\"learn\"><userinput> "
"जानातु</userinput></link> षष्ठखण्डे ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:6
#, no-c-format
msgid "The Grammar of &turtlescript;"
msgstr "&turtlescript इत्यस्य व्याकरणम्;"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:7
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"As in any language, &turtlescript; has different types of words and symbols. "
"In English we distinguish verbs (like 'to walk' or 'to sing') and nouns "
"(like 'sister' or 'house'), they are used for different purposes. "
"&turtlescript; is a programming language, it is used to instruct &kturtle; "
"what to do."
msgstr ""
"यथा कस्यापि भाषायां, &turtlescript; भिन्नप्रकाराः शब्दाः प्रतीकाः च सन्ति । "
"आङ्ग्लभाषायां वयं क्रियापदानां (यथा 'चलितुं' अथवा 'गातुं') तथा संज्ञानां (यथा 'भगिनी' "
"अथवा 'गृहम्') भेदं कुर्मः, तेषां प्रयोगः भिन्नप्रयोजनाय भवति। &कच्छपलिपि; प्रोग्रामिंग् भाषा "
"अस्ति, तस्याः उपयोगः &kturtle; किं कर्तव्यम् ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:8
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In this section some of &turtlescript;'s different types of words and "
"symbols are briefly explained. We explain <link linkend=\"comment"
"\">comments</link>, <link linkend=\"command\">commands</link> and the three "
"different kinds of literals: <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"string\">strings</link> and <link linkend=\"boolean-value"
"\">boolean (true/false) values</link>."
msgstr ""
"अस्मिन् खण्डे &amp;turtlescript; इत्यस्य केचन भिन्नप्रकाराः शब्दाः प्रतीकाः च संक्षेपेण "
"व्याख्याताः सन्ति । वयं व्याख्यास्यामः<link linkend=\"comment\"> टिप्पणीं करोति</"
"link> , ९.<link linkend=\"command\"> आदेशाः</link> शाब्दिकानां च त्रयः भिन्नाः "
"प्रकाराः- १.<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्याः</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"string"
"\"> ताराः</link> तथा<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन (सत्य/असत्य) "
"मूल्यानि</link> ."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:12
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comments"
msgstr "टिप्पणियाँ"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:13
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A program consists instructions that are executed when the program is run "
"and so called comments. Comments are not executed, &kturtle; simply ignores "
"them when executing your program. Comment are there for other programmers to "
"make them understand your program better. Everything that follows on a "
"<userinput>#</userinput> symbol is considered a comment in &turtlescript;. "
"For example this little program that does nothing: <screen>\n"
"# this little program does nothing, it is only a comment!\n"
"</screen> It is a bit useless but it explain the matter well."
msgstr ""
"कार्यक्रमे ते निर्देशाः सन्ति ये कार्यक्रमस्य चालनसमये निष्पादिताः भवन्ति तथा च टिप्पण्याः "
"तथाकथिताः । टिप्पण्याः न निष्पाद्यन्ते, &kturtle; केवलं भवतः कार्यक्रमस्य निष्पादनकाले "
"तान् उपेक्षते । अन्येषां प्रोग्रामर्-जनानाम् कृते टिप्पणीः सन्ति येन ते भवतः कार्यक्रमं अधिकतया "
"अवगन्तुं शक्नुवन्ति । <userinput>#</userinput> चिह्ने यत् किमपि अनुवर्तते तत् सर्वं "
"&turtlescript; उदाहरणार्थं एषः लघुः कार्यक्रमः यः किमपि न करोति: <screen>\n"
"# अयं लघु कार्यक्रमः किमपि न करोति, केवलं टिप्पणी एव!\n"
"</screen> किञ्चित् व्यर्थं किन्तु विषयं सम्यक् व्याख्यायते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:16
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Comments get very useful when the program gets a little bit more complex. It "
"can help to give some advice to other programmers. In the following program "
"you see comments being used together with the <link linkend=\"print\">print</"
"link> command. <screen>\n"
"# this program has been made by Cies Breijs.\n"
"print \"this text will get printed on the canvas\"\n"
"# the previous line is not a comment, but the next line is:\n"
"# print \"this text will not get printed!\"\n"
"</screen> The first line describes the program. The second line is executed "
"by &kturtle; and prints <userinput>this text will get printed on the canvas</"
"userinput> on the canvas. The third line is a comment. And the forth line is "
"a comment that contains a piece of &turtlescript;, if the <userinput>#</"
"userinput> symbol would be removed on the fourth line the print statement "
"will we executed by &kturtle;. Programmers say: the print statement on the "
"fourth line is 'commented out'."
msgstr ""
"यदा कार्यक्रमः किञ्चित् अधिकं जटिलः भवति तदा टिप्पण्याः अतीव उपयोगिनो भवन्ति। अन्येभ्यः "
"प्रोग्रामरेभ्यः किञ्चित् सल्लाहं दातुं साहाय्यं कर्तुं शक्नोति । निम्नलिखित कार्यक्रमे भवन्तः "
"टिप्पण्याः एकत्र प्रयुक्ताः पश्यन्ति<link linkend=\"print\"> मुद्रणम्</link> आदेश।"
"<screen> # अयं कार्यक्रमः Cies Breijs इत्यनेन निर्मितः अस्ति। print &quot;एषः पाठः "
"कैनवासे मुद्रितः भविष्यति&quot; # पूर्वपङ्क्तिः टिप्पणी नास्ति, परन्तु अग्रिमपङ्क्तिः अस्ति: "
"# print &quot;एषः पाठः मुद्रितः न भविष्यति!&quot;</screen> प्रथमपङ्क्तौ कार्यक्रमस्य "
"वर्णनं भवति । द्वितीया पङ्क्तिः &amp;kturtle; तथा मुद्रयति<userinput> एषः पाठः "
"कैनवासस्य उपरि मुद्रितः भविष्यति</userinput> कैनवासस्य उपरि । तृतीया पङ्क्तिः टिप्पणी "
"अस्ति। चतुर्थपङ्क्तिश्च टिप्पण्या यस्मिन् &amp;turtlescript;इत्यस्य खण्डः भवति, यदि..."
"<userinput> # # .</userinput> चिह्नं चतुर्थे पङ्क्तौ निष्कासितम् स्यात् print statement "
"will we executed by &amp;kturtle;. प्रोग्रामरः वदन्ति : चतुर्थपङ्क्तौ मुद्रितवक्तव्यं "
"&#39;commented out&#39; इति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:19
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Commented lines are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with light gray in "
"the <link linkend=\"the-editor\">code editor</link>."
msgstr ""
"टिप्पणीकृताः पङ्क्तयः सन्ति<glossterm> प्रकाशितम्</glossterm> लघुधूसरवर्णेन सह<link "
"linkend=\"the-editor\"> कोड सम्पादक</link> ."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:23 programming-reference.docbook:162
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commands"
msgstr "आदेशाः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:24
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using commands you tell the turtle or &kturtle; to do something. Some "
"commands need input, some give output. <screen>\n"
"# forward is a command that needs input, in this case the number 100:\n"
"forward 100\n"
"</screen> The first line is a <link linkend=\"comment\">comment</link>. The "
"second line contains the <userinput>forward</userinput> command and the "
"<link linkend=\"number\">number</link> <userinput>100</userinput>. The "
"number is not part of command, it is considered 'input' for the command."
msgstr ""
"आदेशानां उपयोगेन भवन्तः कच्छपं वा &amp;kturtle; किमपि कर्तुं । केषाञ्चन आदेशानां निवेशस्य "
"आवश्यकता भवति, केचन आउटपुट् ददति ।<screen> # forward इति आदेशः यस्य निवेशस्य आवश्यकता "
"भवति, अस्मिन् सन्दर्भे 100 इति संख्या: forward 100</screen> प्रथमा पङ्क्तिः क<link "
"linkend=\"comment\"> टिप्पणी</link> . द्वितीया पङ्क्तिः अस्ति<userinput> अग्रतः</"
"userinput> आज्ञा च<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link><userinput> १००</"
"userinput> . संख्या आदेशस्य भागः नास्ति, आदेशस्य कृते &#39;निवेशः&#39; इति मन्यते।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:27
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Some commands like &eg; <userinput>go</userinput> need more than one input "
"value. Multiple values have to be separated using the <userinput>,</"
"userinput> character (comma)."
msgstr ""
"केचन आदेशाः यथा &eg; <userinput>go</userinput> इत्यस्य एकादशाधिकं निवेशमूल्यं आवश्यकम् "
"। <userinput>,</userinput> वर्णस्य (comma) उपयोगेन बहुमूल्यानि पृथक् कर्तव्यानि सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:28
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"For a detailed overview of all commands that &kturtle; supports go <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">here</link>. Built-in commands are "
"<glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> in dark blue."
msgstr ""
"सर्वेषां आदेशानां विस्तृतविवरणार्थं यत् &amp;kturtle; समर्थनानि गच्छन्ति<link linkend="
"\"commands\"> अत्र</link> . अन्तर्निर्मिताः आदेशाः सन्ति<glossterm> प्रकाशितम्</"
"glossterm> श्यामनीले ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:32
#, no-c-format
msgid "Numbers"
msgstr "संख्याः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:33
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Most likely you already know quite a bit about numbers. The way numbers are "
"used in &kturtle; is not much different from spoken language, or math."
msgstr ""
"अधिकतया भवन्तः पूर्वमेव संख्यानां विषये किञ्चित् जानन्ति। यथा &kturtle; न तु "
"वाच्यभाषायाः, गणितस्य वा बहु भिन्नम्।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:34
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"We have the so called natural numbers: <userinput>0</userinput>, "
"<userinput>1</userinput>, <userinput>2</userinput>, <userinput>3</"
"userinput>, <userinput>4</userinput>, <userinput>5</userinput>, &etc; The "
"negative numbers: <userinput>-1</userinput>, <userinput>-2</userinput>, "
"<userinput>-3</userinput>, &etc; And the numbers with decimals, or dot-"
"numbers, for example: <userinput>0.1</userinput>, <userinput>3.14</"
"userinput>, <userinput>33.3333</userinput>, <userinput>-5.05</userinput>, "
"<userinput>-1.0</userinput>. The <userinput>.</userinput> character (dot) is "
"used as decimal separator."
msgstr ""
"अस्माकं तथाकथिताः प्राकृतिकाः सङ्ख्याः सन्ति : <userinput>0</userinput>, "
"<userinput>1</userinput>, <userinput>2</userinput>, <userinput>3</"
"userinput>, <userinput>4</ userinput>, <usrinput>5</usrinput>, इत्यादि; "
"ऋणात्मकसङ्ख्याः : <userinput>-1</userinput>, <userinput>-2</userinput>, "
"<userinput>-3</userinput>, इत्यादयः; दशमलवयुक्ताः च सङ्ख्याः, अथवा बिन्दु-सङ्ख्याः, "
"यथा- <userinput>0.1</userinput>, <userinput>3.14</userinput>, "
"<userinput>33.3333</userinput>, <userinput>-5.05</userinput> इति , "
"<उपयोगकर्ता>-1.0</usrinput> । <userinput>.</userinput> वर्णः (dot) "
"दशमलवविभाजकरूपेण उपयुज्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:37
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Numbers can be used in <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">mathematical "
"operators</link> and <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparison "
"operators</link>. They can also be stored in <link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\">variables</link>. Numbers are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> "
"in dark red."
msgstr ""
"संख्यानां उपयोगः कर्तुं शक्यते<link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\"> गणितीय "
"संचालक</link> तथा<link linkend=\"comparing-operators\"> तुलना संचालकाः</link> . "
"तेषां संग्रहणं अपि कर्तुं शक्यते<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चराः</"
"link> . संख्याः सन्ति<glossterm> प्रकाशितम्</glossterm> कृष्णरक्तवर्णे ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:43
#, no-c-format
msgid "Strings"
msgstr "ताराः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:44
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First an example: <screen>\n"
"print \"Hello, I'm a string.\"\n"
"</screen> In this example <userinput>print</userinput> is a command where "
"<userinput>\"Hello, I'm a string.\"</userinput> is a string. Strings start "
"and end with the <userinput>\"</userinput> mark, by these marks &kturtle; "
"knows it is a string."
msgstr ""
"प्रथमं उदाहरणम् : <screen>\n"
"print \"नमस्ते, अहं तारः अस्मि।\"\n"
"</screen> अस्मिन् उदाहरणे <userinput>print</userinput> एकः आदेशः अस्ति यत्र "
"<userinput>\"नमस्ते, अहं स्ट्रिंग् अस्मि।\"</userinput> इति स्ट्रिंग् अस्ति । ताराः "
"<userinput>\"</userinput> चिह्नेन आरभ्यन्ते समाप्ताः च, एतैः चिह्नैः &kturtle; स्ट्रिंग् "
"इति जानाति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:47
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Strings can be put in <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</"
"link>, just like <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link>. Yet, unlike "
"numbers, strings cannot be used in <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators"
"\">mathematical operators</link> or <link linkend=\"comparing-operators"
"\">comparison operators</link>. Strings are <glossterm>highlighted</"
"glossterm> with red."
msgstr ""
"ताराः स्थापयितुं शक्यन्ते<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चराः</link> , "
"यथा<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्याः</link> . तथापि संख्यानां विपरीतम्, स्ट्रिंग् "
"इत्यस्य उपयोगः कर्तुं न शक्यते<link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\"> गणितीय "
"संचालक</link> वा<link linkend=\"comparing-operators\"> तुलना संचालकाः</link> . "
"ताराः सन्ति<glossterm> प्रकाशितम्</glossterm> रक्तेन सह ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:51
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boolean (true/false) values"
msgstr "बूलियन (सत्य/असत्य) मूल्यानि"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:52
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are only two boolean values: <userinput>true</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>true</primary></indexterm> and "
"<userinput>false</userinput><indexterm><primary>false</primary></indexterm>. "
"Sometimes they are also called: <quote><userinput>on</userinput></quote> and "
"<quote><userinput>off</userinput></quote>, <quote><userinput>yes</"
"userinput></quote> and <quote><userinput>no</userinput></quote>, "
"<quote><userinput>one</userinput></quote> and <quote><userinput>zero</"
"userinput></quote>. But in &turtlescript; we call them, always, "
"<userinput>true</userinput> and <userinput>false</userinput>. Have a look at "
"this piece of &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$a = true\n"
"</screen> If you look in the <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</"
"link> you can see that the <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables"
"\">variable</link> <userinput>$a</userinput> is set to <userinput>true</"
"userinput>, and has the boolean type."
msgstr ""
"केवलं द्वौ बूलियनमूल्यौ स्तः :<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput><indexterm><primary> "
"सत्यम्‌</primary></indexterm> तथा<userinput> असत्य</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary> असत्य</primary></indexterm> . कदाचित् ते इत्यपि "
"उच्यन्ते- १.<quote><userinput> इत्युपरि</userinput></quote> तथा<quote><userinput> "
"दूरे</userinput></quote> , ९.<quote><userinput> आम्‌</userinput></quote> "
"तथा<quote><userinput> नहि</userinput></quote> , ९.<quote><userinput> एकम्‌</"
"userinput></quote> तथा<quote><userinput> शून्य</userinput></quote> . परन्तु &amp;"
"turtlescript; वयं तान् वदामः, सर्वदा,<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> "
"तथा<userinput> असत्य</userinput> . &amp;turtlescript;: इत्यस्य एतत् खण्डं पश्यन्तु।"
"<screen> $क = सत्यम्</screen> यदि त्वं पश्यसि<link linkend=\"the-inspector\"> "
"निरीक्षकः</link> भवन्तः द्रष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति यत्...<link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\"> चरः</link><userinput> $क</userinput> इति सेट् भवति<userinput> "
"सत्यम्‌</userinput> , तथा च बूलियन प्रकारः अस्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:55
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Often boolean values are the result of a <link linkend=\"comparing-operators"
"\">comparison operator</link>, like in the following piece of "
"&turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$answer = 10 &gt; 3\n"
"</screen> The <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> "
"<userinput>$answer</userinput> is set to <userinput>true</userinput> because "
"<userinput>10</userinput> is larger than <userinput>3</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"प्रायः बूलियनमूल्यानि क<link linkend=\"comparing-operators\"> तुलना संचालकः</"
"link> , यथा &amp;turtlescript; इत्यस्य निम्नलिखितखण्डे:<screen> $उत्तर = १० &gt; "
"३</screen> द<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चरः</link><userinput> "
"$उत्तरम्</userinput> इति सेट् भवति<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> यतः<userinput> "
"१०</userinput> इत्यस्मात् बृहत्तरः अस्ति<userinput> ३</userinput> ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:58
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Boolean values, <userinput>true</userinput> and <userinput>false</"
"userinput>, are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with dark red."
msgstr ""
"बूलियनमूल्यानि, <userinput>true</userinput> तथा <userinput>false</userinput>, "
"गहरे रक्तेन <glossterm>प्रकाशितानि</glossterm> सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:66
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mathematical, boolean and comparing operators"
msgstr "गणितीय, बूलियन तथा तुलनात्मक संचालक"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:67
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The title of this section might sound very difficult, yet it is not as "
"difficult as it sound."
msgstr "अस्य खण्डस्य शीर्षकं अतीव कठिनं ध्वन्यते, तथापि न तावत् कठिनं यथा ध्वनितुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:70
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mathematical operators"
msgstr "गणितीय संचालक"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:71
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These are the basic math symbols known as: add (<userinput>+</userinput>), "
"subtract (<userinput>-</userinput>), multiply (<userinput>*</userinput>), "
"divide (<userinput>/</userinput>) and power (<userinput>^</userinput>)."
msgstr ""
"एते मूलभूतगणितचिह्नानि सन्ति : योजयतु (<userinput>+</userinput>), घटयतु "
"(<userinput>-</userinput>), गुणयतु (<userinput>*</userinput>), विभाजयतु "
"(<userinput> /</userinput>) तथा शक्ति (<userinput>^</userinput>) ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:73
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here a small example of the mathematical operators you can use in "
"&turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$add      = 1 + 1\n"
"$subtract = 20 - 5\n"
"$multiply = 15 * 2\n"
"$divide   = 30 / 30\n"
"$power    = 2 ^ 2\n"
"</screen> The values resulting from the mathematical operations get <link "
"linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">assigned</link> to various <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</link>. Using the <link linkend=\"the-"
"inspector\">inspector</link> you can see the values."
msgstr ""
"अत्र गणितीयसञ्चालकानां लघु उदाहरणं यत् भवन्तः &amp;turtlescript;: इत्यत्र उपयोक्तुं "
"शक्नुवन्ति:<screen> $जोड = 1 + 1 $घटा = 20 - 5 $गुण = 15 * 2 $विभाजन = 30 / 30 "
"$शक्ति = 2 ^ 2</screen> गणितीयक्रियाणां परिणामरूपेण प्राप्तानि मूल्यानि "
"प्राप्नुवन्ति<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> नियुक्तः</link> विविधं "
"प्रति<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चराः</link> . प्रयुज्य<link "
"linkend=\"the-inspector\"> निरीक्षकः</link> मूल्यानि द्रष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:76
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you just want a simple calculation to be done you can do something like "
"this:"
msgstr "यदि भवान् केवलं सरलं गणनां कर्तुम् इच्छति तर्हि भवान् एतादृशं किमपि कर्तुं शक्नोति:"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:77
#, no-c-format
msgid "print 2010-12"
msgstr "print 2010-12"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:78
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Now an example with parentheses: <screen>\n"
"print ( ( 20 - 5 ) * 2 / 30 ) + 1\n"
"</screen> The expressions inside parentheses will be calculated first. In "
"this example, 20-5 will be calculated, then multiplied by 2, divided by 30, "
"and then 1 is added (giving 2). Parentheses can also be used in other cases."
msgstr ""
"अधुना कोष्ठकेन सह उदाहरणम् : <screen>\n"
"मुद्रण ( ( २० - ५ ) * २ / ३० ) + १\n"
"</screen> कोष्ठकानां अन्तः व्यञ्जनानां प्रथमं गणना भविष्यति । अस्मिन् उदाहरणे २०-५ गण्यते, "
"ततः २ गुणितं भविष्यति, ३० इत्यनेन विभक्तं भवति, ततः १ योज्यते (२ दत्त्वा) । अन्येषु अपि "
"कोष्ठकानां प्रयोगः कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:81
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"&kturtle; also has more advanced mathematical features in the form of "
"commands. Have a look at the following commands but be aware that it "
"concerns advanced operations: <link linkend=\"round\">round</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"random\">random</link>, <link linkend=\"sqrt\">sqrt</link> , <link "
"linkend=\"pi\">pi</link>, <link linkend=\"sin\">sin</link>, <link linkend="
"\"cos\">cos</link>, <link linkend=\"tan\">tan</link>, <link linkend=\"arcsin"
"\">arcsin</link>, <link linkend=\"arccos\">arccos</link>, <link linkend="
"\"arctan\">arctan</link>."
msgstr ""
"&amp;kturtle; अपि च आदेशरूपेण अधिकानि उन्नतानि गणितीयविशेषतानि सन्ति । निम्नलिखित "
"आदेशान् अवलोकयन्तु परन्तु अवगच्छन्तु यत् एतत् उन्नतसञ्चालनानां विषये अस्ति:<link linkend="
"\"round\"> वृत्त</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"random\"> यदृच्छासङ्ख्या</link> , ९."
"<link linkend=\"sqrt\"> sqrt</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"pi\"> पि० पि०</"
"link> , ९.<link linkend=\"sin\"> पापम्</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"cos\"> कोस्</"
"link> , ९.<link linkend=\"tan\"> तन्</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"arcsin\"> "
"आर्कसिन्</link> , ९.<link linkend=\"arccos\"> आर्कोस्</link> , ९.<link linkend="
"\"arctan\"> आर्कटन</link> ."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:87
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boolean (true/false) operators"
msgstr "बूलियन (सत्य/असत्य) संचालक"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:88
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Where <link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\">mathematical operators</link> "
"are mainly for <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link>, boolean operators "
"are for <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean values</link> "
"(<userinput>true</userinput> and <userinput>false</userinput>). There are "
"only three boolean operators, namely: <userinput>and</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>and</primary></indexterm>, <userinput>or</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>or</primary></indexterm>, and <userinput>not</"
"userinput><indexterm><primary>not</primary></indexterm>. The following piece "
"of &turtlescript; shows how to use them: <screen>\n"
"$and_1_1 = true and true    # -> true\n"
"$and_1_0 = true and false   # -> false\n"
"$and_0_1 = false and true   # -> false\n"
"$and_0_0 = false and false  # -> false\n"
"\n"
"$or_1_1 = true or true    # -> true\n"
"$or_1_0 = true or false   # -> true\n"
"$or_0_1 = false or true   # -> true\n"
"$or_0_0 = false or false  # -> false\n"
"\n"
"$not_1 = not true   # -> false\n"
"$not_0 = not false  # -> true\n"
"</screen> Using the <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</link> you can "
"see the values, yet we also supply these results as little comments at the "
"end of the lines. <userinput>and</userinput> evaluates <userinput>true</"
"userinput> only if both sides are <userinput>true</userinput>. "
"<userinput>or</userinput> evaluates <userinput>true</userinput> if either "
"side is <userinput>true</userinput>. And <userinput>not</userinput> turns a "
"<userinput>true</userinput> into <userinput>false</userinput> and a "
"<userinput>false</userinput> into <userinput>true</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"कुत्र<link linkend=\"mathematical-operators\"> गणितीय संचालक</link> मुख्यतया कृते "
"भवन्ति<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्याः</link> , बूलियन-सञ्चालकाः कृते सन्ति<link "
"linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन मूल्यानि</link> (<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> "
"तथा<userinput> असत्य</userinput> ). केवलं त्रयः बूलियन-सञ्चालकाः सन्ति, यथा-"
"<userinput> तथा</userinput><indexterm><primary> तथा</primary></indexterm> , "
"९.<userinput> वा</userinput><indexterm><primary> वा</primary></indexterm> , "
"तथा<userinput> नहि</userinput><indexterm><primary> नहि</primary></"
"indexterm> . &amp;turtlescript इत्यस्य निम्नलिखितखण्डः; तेषां उपयोगः कथं करणीयः इति "
"दर्शयति : १.<screen> $तथा_1_1 = सत्यं सत्यं च # -&gt; सत्यं $तथा_1_0 = सत्यं असत्यं च # "
"-&gt; मिथ्या $तथा_0_1 = असत्यं सत्यं च # -&gt; मिथ्या $तथा_0_0 = मिथ्या च असत्यं # -"
"&gt; मिथ्या $or_1_1 = सत्यं वा सत्यं वा # -&gt; सत्यम् $or_1_0 = सत्यम् अथवा असत्यम् # -"
"&gt; सत्यम् $or_0_1 = मिथ्या वा सत्यम् # -&gt; true $or_0_0 = मिथ्या अथवा असत्यम् # -"
"&gt; false $not_1 = सत्यं नास्ति # -&gt; false $not_0 = असत्यं न # -&gt; सत्यम्</"
"screen> प्रयुज्य<link linkend=\"the-inspector\"> निरीक्षकः</link> मूल्यानि द्रष्टुं "
"शक्नुवन्ति, तथापि वयं एतानि परिणामानि पङ्क्तयः अन्ते अल्पानि टिप्पण्यानि अपि आपूर्तिं कुर्मः "
"।<userinput> तथा</userinput> मूल्याङ्कनं करोति<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> केवलं "
"यदि उभयपक्षः भवति<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> .<userinput> वा</userinput> "
"मूल्याङ्कनं करोति<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> यदि पक्षयोः एकः अस्ति<userinput> "
"सत्यम्‌</userinput> . तथा<userinput> नहि</userinput> परिवर्तते क<userinput> सत्यम्‌</"
"userinput> इत्यस्मिन्‌<userinput> असत्य</userinput> तथा क<userinput> असत्य</"
"userinput> इत्यस्मिन्‌<userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:91
#, no-c-format
msgid "Boolean operators are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with pink."
msgstr "बूलियन-सञ्चालकाः गुलाबी-वर्णेन <glossterm>प्रकाशिताः</glossterm> भवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:94
#, no-c-format
msgid "Some more advanced examples"
msgstr "केचन अधिकाः उन्नताः उदाहरणानि"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:95
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider the following example with <userinput>and</userinput>: <screen>\n"
"$a = 1\n"
"$b = 5\n"
"if (($a &lt; 10) and ($b == 5)) and ($a &lt; $b) {\n"
"  print \"hello\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> In this piece of &turtlescript; the result of three <link linkend="
"\"comparing-operators\">comparing operators</link> are merged using "
"<userinput>and</userinput> operators. This means that all three have to "
"evaluate <quote>true</quote> in order for the <quote>hello</quote> to be "
"printed."
msgstr ""
"सह निम्नलिखित उदाहरणं विचार्यताम्<userinput> तथा</userinput> : १.<screen> $a = 1 "
"$b = 5 यदि (($a &lt; 10) तथा ($b == 5)) तथा ($a &lt; $b) { print &quot;"
"hello&quot; }</screen> अस्मिन् &amp;turtlescript; त्रयाणां परिणामः<link linkend="
"\"comparing-operators\"> संचालकानाम् तुलनां कुर्वन्</link> उपयोगेन विलीनाः "
"भवन्ति<userinput> तथा</userinput> संचालकाः । त्रयाणां मूल्याङ्कनं कर्तव्यमिति "
"भावः<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> यथाक्रमम्<quote> नमस्ते</quote> मुद्रितव्य इति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:99
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"An example with <userinput>or</userinput>: <screen>\n"
"$n = 1\n"
"if ($n &lt; 10) or ($n == 2) {\n"
"  print \"hello\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> In this piece of &turtlescript; the left side of the "
"<userinput>or</userinput> is evaluating to <quote>true</quote>, the right "
"side to <quote>false</quote>. Since one of the two sides of the "
"<userinput>or</userinput> operator is <quote>true</quote>, the "
"<userinput>or</userinput> operator evaluates <quote>true</quote>. That means "
"<quote>hello</quote> gets printed."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>अथवा</userinput> इत्यनेन सह उदाहरणम्: <screen>\n"
"$न = 1\n"
"यदि ($n &lt; 10) अथवा ($n == 2) {\n"
"  print \"नमस्ते\"।\n"
"} .\n"
"</screen> अस्मिन् &turtlescript; <userinput>स्य वा</userinput> इत्यस्य वामभागः "
"<quote>true</quote> इति मूल्याङ्कनं करोति, दक्षिणभागः <quote>false</quote> इति । "
"यतः <userinput>अथवा</userinput> संचालकस्य द्वयोः पक्षयोः एकः <quote>true</quote> "
"अस्ति, <userinput>अथवा</userinput> संचालकः <quote>true</quote> इति मूल्याङ्कनं "
"करोति । तस्य अर्थः <quote>hello</quote> मुद्रितं भवति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:103
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"And finally an example with <userinput>not</userinput> which changes "
"<quote>true</quote> into <quote>false</quote> and <quote>false</quote> into "
"<quote>true</quote>. Have a look:"
msgstr ""
"अन्ते च <userinput>not</userinput> इत्यनेन सह उदाहरणं यत् <quote>true</quote> इति "
"<quote>false</quote> इति परिवर्तयति तथा च <quote>false</quote> इति "
"<quote>true</quote> इति परिवर्तयति . एकवारं पश्यन्तु :"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:104
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$n = 1\n"
"if not ($n == 3) {\n"
"  print \"hello\"\n"
"} else {\n"
"  print \"not hello ;-)\"\n"
"}"
msgstr ""
"$न = 1\n"
"यदि न ($n == 3) {\n"
"  print \"नमस्ते\"।\n"
"} उत {\n"
"  print \"न नमस्कार ;-)\"।\n"
"} ."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:109
#, no-c-format
msgid "Comparing operators"
msgstr "संचालकानाम् तुलनां कुर्वन्"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:110
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Consider this simple comparison: <screen>\n"
"$answer = 10 &gt; 3\n"
"</screen> Here <userinput>10</userinput> is compared to <userinput>3</"
"userinput> with the <quote>greater than</quote> operator. The result of this "
"comparison, the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean value</link> "
"<userinput>true</userinput> is stored in the <link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\">variable</link> <userinput>$answer</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"एतां सरलं तुलनां विचार्यताम् : १.<screen> $उत्तर = १० &gt; ३</screen> "
"अत्र<userinput> १०</userinput> इति तुल्यते<userinput> ३</userinput> सह<quote> "
"अस्मात् महत्तरम्</quote> संचालकः । अस्याः तुलनायाः परिणामः, द<link linkend="
"\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन मूल्य</link><userinput> सत्यम्‌</userinput> इति "
"संगृह्यते<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चरः</link><userinput> "
"$उत्तरम्</userinput> ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:113
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"All <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link> and <link linkend=\"assignment-"
"of-variables\">variables</link> (that contain numbers) can be compared to "
"each other with comparing operators."
msgstr ""
"सर्वे<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्याः</link> तथा<link linkend=\"assignment-of-"
"variables\"> चराः</link> (येषु संख्याः सन्ति) तुलनात्मकसञ्चालकैः सह परस्परं तुलना कर्तुं "
"शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:114
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Here are all possible comparing operators: <table> <title>Types of "
"questions</title> <tgroup cols=\"3\"> <tbody> <row> <entry><userinput>$A == "
"$B</userinput></entry> <entry>equals</entry> <entry>answer is <quote>true</"
"quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> equals <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> "
"</row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A != $B</userinput></entry> <entry>not-"
"equals</entry> <entry>answer is <quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</"
"userinput> does not equal <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> "
"<entry><userinput>$A &gt; $B</userinput></entry> <entry>greater than</entry> "
"<entry>answer is <quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is greater "
"than <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A "
"&lt; $B</userinput></entry> <entry>smaller than</entry> <entry>answer is "
"<quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is smaller than <userinput>"
"$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A &gt;= $B</"
"userinput></entry> <entry>greater than or equals</entry> <entry>answer is "
"<quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is greater than or equals "
"<userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> <row> <entry><userinput>$A &lt;= "
"$B</userinput></entry> <entry>smaller than or equals</entry> <entry>answer "
"is <quote>true</quote> if <userinput>$A</userinput> is smaller than or "
"equals <userinput>$B</userinput></entry> </row> </tbody> </tgroup> </table> "
"Please note that <userinput>$A</userinput> and <userinput>$B</userinput> "
"have to be <link linkend=\"number\">numbers</link> or <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">variables</link> that contain numbers."
msgstr ""
"अत्र सर्वे सम्भवाः तुलनासञ्चालकाः सन्ति :<table><title> प्रश्नप्रकाराः</title><tgroup "
"cols=\"3\"><tbody><row><entry><userinput> $A == $B</userinput></"
"entry><entry> समः</entry><entry> उत्तरम् इति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> "
"यदि<userinput> $A</userinput> समः<userinput> $B</userinput></entry></"
"row><row><entry><userinput> $A != $B</userinput></entry><entry> न-समानाः</"
"entry><entry> उत्तरम् इति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> यदि<userinput> $A</userinput> न "
"समं करोति<userinput> $B</userinput></entry></row><row><entry><userinput> $A "
"&gt; $B</userinput></entry><entry> अस्मात् महत्तरम्</entry><entry> उत्तरम् "
"इति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> यदि<userinput> $A</userinput> इत्यस्मात् अधिकं "
"भवति<userinput> $B</userinput></entry></row><row><entry><userinput> $A &lt; "
"$B</userinput></entry><entry> लघुतरम्</entry><entry> उत्तरम् इति<quote> सत्यम्‌</"
"quote> यदि<userinput> $A</userinput> इत्यस्मात् लघुतरः अस्ति<userinput> $B</"
"userinput></entry></row><row><entry><userinput> $A &gt;= $B</userinput></"
"entry><entry> अधिकाधिकं वा समं वा</entry><entry> उत्तरम् इति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> "
"यदि<userinput> $A</userinput> अधिकः समः वा भवति<userinput> $B</userinput></"
"entry></row><row><entry><userinput> $A &lt;= $B</userinput></entry><entry> "
"लघुतरं वा समं वा</entry><entry> उत्तरम् इति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> यदि<userinput> "
"$A</userinput> अपेक्षया लघुतरः समः वा भवति<userinput> $B</userinput></entry></"
"row></tbody></tgroup></table> कृपया तत् अवलोकयन्तु<userinput> $A</userinput> "
"तथा<userinput> $B</userinput> भवितव्यम् अस्ति<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्याः</"
"link> वा<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चराः</link> येषु संख्याः सन्ति।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:163
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using commands you tell the turtle or &kturtle; to do something. Some "
"commands need input, some give output. In this section we explain all the "
"built-in commands of &kturtle;. Alternatively, using <link linkend=\"learn"
"\"><userinput>learn</userinput></link>, you can create your own commands. "
"Built-in commands we discuss here are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> "
"with dark blue."
msgstr ""
"आदेशानां उपयोगेन भवन्तः कच्छपं वा &amp;kturtle; किमपि कर्तुं । केषाञ्चन आदेशानां निवेशस्य "
"आवश्यकता भवति, केचन आउटपुट् ददति । अस्मिन् खण्डे वयं &amp;kturtle; इत्यस्य सर्वाणि "
"अन्तःनिर्मितानि आदेशानि व्याख्यास्यामः । वैकल्पिकरूपेण, उपयोगेन<link linkend=\"learn"
"\"><userinput> जानातु</userinput></link> , भवान् स्वकीयान् आदेशान् निर्मातुम् अर्हति । "
"अत्र वयं चर्चां कुर्मः अन्तर्निर्मित-आदेशाः सन्ति<glossterm> प्रकाशितम्</glossterm> "
"श्यामनीलेन सह ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:166
#, no-c-format
msgid "Moving the turtle"
msgstr "कच्छपं चालयन्"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:167
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several commands to move the turtle over the screen."
msgstr "कच्छपं पटलस्य उपरि चालयितुं अनेकाः आदेशाः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>forward (fw)</term>"
msgstr "<term>अग्रे (fw)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:172
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>forward (fw)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>अग्रे (fw)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid "forward X"
msgstr "अग्रे X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:173
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>forward</userinput> moves the turtle forward by the amount of X "
"pixels. When the pen is down the turtle will leave a trail. "
"<userinput>forward</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>fw</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>forward</userinput> कच्छपं X पिक्सेलस्य परिमाणेन अग्रे चालयति । यदा लेखनी "
"अधः भवति तदा कच्छपः एकं पन्थानं त्यक्ष्यति। <userinput>forward</userinput> इति "
"संक्षिप्तं <userinput>fw</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>backward (bw)</term>"
msgstr "<term>पश्चात् (bw)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:180
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>backward (bw)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पश्चाद् (bw)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid "backward X"
msgstr "पश्चात्ताप X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:181
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>backward</userinput> moves the turtle backward by the amount of X "
"pixels. When the pen is down the turtle will leave a trail. "
"<userinput>backward</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>bw</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>backward</userinput> कच्छपं X पिक्सेलस्य परिमाणेन पश्चात् चालयति । यदा "
"लेखनी अधः भवति तदा कच्छपः एकं पन्थानं त्यक्ष्यति। <userinput>backward</userinput> "
"इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>bw</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>turnleft (tl)</term>"
msgstr "<पदं>वामं (tl)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:188
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>turnleft (tl)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>वाम (tl)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid "turnleft X"
msgstr "turnleft X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:189
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput> commands the turtle to turn an amount of X "
"degrees to the left. <userinput>turnleft</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>tl</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput> कच्छपं X डिग्री परिमाणं वामभागे भ्रमितुं आज्ञापयति । "
"<userinput>turnleft</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>tl</userinput> इति कर्तुं "
"शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>turnright (tr)</term>"
msgstr "<term>turnright (त्र)</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:196
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>turnright (tr)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>दक्षिणं (त्र)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid "turnright X"
msgstr "turnright X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:197
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>turnright</userinput> the turtle to turn an amount of X degrees "
"to the right. <userinput>turnright</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>tr</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>turnright</userinput> कच्छपं X डिग्री परिमाणं दक्षिणतः परिवर्तयितुं । "
"<userinput>turnright</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>tr</userinput> इति "
"कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>direction (dir)</term>"
msgstr "<पद>दिशा (dir)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:204
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>direction (dir)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>दिशा (dir)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid "direction X"
msgstr "दिक् X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:205
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>direction</userinput> set the turtle's direction to an amount of "
"X degrees counting from zero, and thus is not relative to the turtle's "
"previous direction. <userinput>direction</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>dir</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>direction</userinput> कच्छपस्य दिशां शून्यात् गणयन् X डिग्री परिमाणं सेट् "
"करोति, एवं च कच्छपस्य पूर्वदिशायाः सापेक्षं न भवति <userinput>दिशा</userinput> इति "
"संक्षिप्तं <userinput>dir</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>getdirection</term>"
msgstr "<term>getdirection</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:212
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>getdirection</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>प्राप्तदिशा</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>getdirection</screen>"
msgstr "<स्क्रीन्>दिशाप्राप्ति</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:213
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>getdirection</userinput> returns the turtle's direction as an "
"amount of degrees counting from zero, where zero is the direction when the "
"turtle is pointing upwards."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>getdirection</userinput> कच्छपस्य दिशां शून्यात् गणयन्त्याः डिग्री-"
"मात्रायाः रूपेण प्रत्यागच्छति, यत्र शून्यं कच्छपस्य ऊर्ध्वं दर्शयति चेत् दिशः भवति"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>center</term>"
msgstr "<पद>केन्द्र</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:220
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>center</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>केन्द्र</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>center</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>केन्द्र</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:221
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>center</userinput> moves the turtle to the center on the canvas."
msgstr "<userinput>center</userinput> कच्छपं कैनवासस्य उपरि केन्द्रं प्रति चालयति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>go</term>"
msgstr "<पद>ग</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:228
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>go</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>ग</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid "go X,Y"
msgstr "गच्छ X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:229
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>go</userinput> commands the turtle to go to a certain place on "
"the canvas. This place is X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> "
"from the left of the canvas, and Y <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</"
"glossterm> from the top of the canvas."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>go</userinput> कच्छपं कैनवासस्य कस्मिंश्चित् स्थानं गन्तुं आज्ञापयति । इदं स्थानं "
"कैनवासस्य वामतः X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">पिक्सेल</glossterm>, कैनवासस्य "
"उपरि Y <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">पिक्सेल</glossterm> च अस्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>gox</term>"
msgstr "<पद>गोक्स</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:236
#, no-c-format
msgid "gox (gx)"
msgstr "गोक्स (gx)"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid "gox X"
msgstr "x"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:237
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>gox</userinput> using this command the turtle will move to X "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> from the left of the canvas "
"whilst staying at the same height. <userinput>gox</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>gx</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>gox</userinput> एतत् आदेशं उपयुज्य कच्छपः समाने ऊर्ध्वतायां स्थित्वा कैनवासस्य "
"वामतः X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> प्रति गमिष्यति । "
"<userinput>gox</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>gx</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते "
"।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>goy</term>"
msgstr "<पद>गोय</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:244
#, no-c-format
msgid "goy (gy)"
msgstr "गोय (गी)"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid "goy Y"
msgstr "गोय Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:245
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>goy</userinput> using this command the turtle will move to Y "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> from the top of the canvas "
"whilst staying at the same distance from the left border of the canvas. "
"<userinput>goy</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>gy</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>goy</userinput> एतत् आदेशं उपयुज्य कच्छपः कैनवासस्य वामसीमातः समानदूरे "
"स्थित्वा कैनवासस्य उपरितः Y <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm> इति "
"गमिष्यति <userinput>goy</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>gy</userinput> इति "
"कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:249
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Using the commands <userinput>go</userinput>, <userinput>gox</userinput>, "
"<userinput>goy</userinput> and <userinput>center</userinput> the turtle will "
"not draw a line, no matter if the pen is up or down."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>go</userinput>, <userinput>gox</userinput>, <userinput>goy</"
"userinput> तथा <userinput>center</userinput> इति आदेशानां उपयोगेन कच्छपः रेखां न "
"आकर्षयिष्यति, यद्यपि... लेखनी उपरि अधः वा भवति।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:254
#, no-c-format
msgid "Where is the turtle?"
msgstr "कच्छपः कुत्र अस्ति ?"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:255
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two commands which return the position of the turtle on the screen."
msgstr "तत्र द्वौ आदेशौ स्तः ये पर्दायां कच्छपस्य स्थितिं प्रत्यागच्छन्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>getx</term>"
msgstr "<term>getx</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:260
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>getx</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिकः>getx</primary> इति"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:261
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>getx</userinput> returns the number of pixels from the left of "
"the canvas to the current position of the turtle."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>getx</userinput> इत्यनेन कैनवासस्य वामतः कच्छपस्य वर्तमानस्थानं प्रति "
"पिक्सेलसङ्ख्यां प्रत्यागच्छति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>gety</term>"
msgstr "<पद>ज्वार</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:268
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>gety</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>गेति</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:269
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>gety</userinput> returns the number of pixels from the top of the "
"canvas to the current position of the turtle."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>gety</userinput> इत्यनेन कैनवासस्य उपरितः कच्छपस्य वर्तमानस्थानं प्रति "
"पिक्सेलसङ्ख्यां प्रत्यागच्छति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:276
#, no-c-format
msgid "The turtle has a pen"
msgstr "कच्छपस्य लेखनी अस्ति"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:277
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The turtle has a pen that draws a line when the turtle moves. There are a "
"few commands to control the pen. In this section we explain these commands."
msgstr ""
"कच्छपस्य एकः लेखनी अस्ति या कच्छपस्य गमनसमये रेखां आकर्षयति । लेखनीं नियन्त्रयितुं कतिचन "
"आदेशाः सन्ति । अस्मिन् खण्डे वयं एतान् आदेशान् व्याख्यास्यामः ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>penup (pu)</term>"
msgstr "<पद>पेनुप (पु)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:281
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>penup (pu)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पेनुप (पु)</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid "penup"
msgstr "पूरकः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:282
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>penup</userinput> lifts the pen from the canvas. When the pen is "
"<quote>up</quote> no line will be drawn when the turtle moves. See also "
"<userinput>pendown</userinput>. <userinput>penup</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>pu</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>penup</userinput> इति लेखनीं कैनवासात् उत्थापयति । यदा लेखनी "
"<quote>ऊर्ध्वं</quote> भवति तदा कच्छपस्य गमनसमये कोऽपि रेखा न आकृष्यते । "
"<userinput>pendown</userinput> इत्यपि पश्यन्तु । <userinput>penup</userinput> "
"इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>pu</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>pendown (pd)</term>"
msgstr "<पद>पण्डन (pd)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:289
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>pendown (pd)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पेनडाउन (pd)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid "pendown"
msgstr "pendown"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:290
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>pendown</userinput> presses the pen down on the canvas. When the "
"pen is press <quote>down</quote> on the canvas a line will be drawn when the "
"turtle moves. See also <userinput>penup</userinput>. <userinput>pendown</"
"userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>pd</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>pendown</userinput> इति लेखनीं कैनवासस्य उपरि अधः निपीडयति । यदा लेखनी "
"कैनवासस्य उपरि <quote>down</quote> नुदति तदा कच्छपस्य गमनसमये रेखा आकृष्यते । "
"<userinput>penup</userinput> इत्यपि पश्यन्तु । <userinput>pendown</userinput> "
"इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>pd</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>penwidth (pw)</term>"
msgstr "<term>पेनविड्थ (pw)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:297
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>penwidth (pw)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पेनविड्थ (pw)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid "penwidth X"
msgstr "पेनविड्थ X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:298
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> sets the width of the pen (the line width) "
"to an amount of X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>. "
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>pw</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> पेनस्य विस्तारं (रेखाविस्तारः) X <glossterm "
"linkend=\"pixels\">पिक्सेल</glossterm> इत्यस्य परिमाणं सेट् करोति । "
"<userinput>penwidth</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>pw</userinput> इति कर्तुं "
"शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>pencolor (pc)</term>"
msgstr "<term>पेनरङ्गः (pc)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:305
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>pencolor (pc)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पेनरङ्ग (pc)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid "pencolor R,G,B"
msgstr "कलम रंग R,G,B"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:306
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> sets the color of the pen. "
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> takes an <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">RGB "
"combination</glossterm> as input. <userinput>pencolor</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>pc</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> इत्यनेन पेनस्य वर्णः सेट् भवति । "
"<userinput>pencolor</userinput> एकं <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">RGB संयोजनं</"
"glossterm> निवेशरूपेण गृह्णाति । <userinput>pencolor</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं "
"<userinput>pc</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:313
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commands to control the canvas"
msgstr "कैनवासं नियन्त्रयितुं आदेशाः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:314
#, no-c-format
msgid "There are several commands to control the canvas."
msgstr "कैनवासस्य नियन्त्रणार्थं अनेकाः आदेशाः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>canvassize (cs)</term>"
msgstr "<term>canvassize (cs)</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:318
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>canvassize (cs)</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>कैनवास (cs)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid "canvassize X,Y"
msgstr "canvasize X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:319
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With the <userinput>canvassize</userinput> command you can set the size of "
"the canvas. It takes X and Y as input, where X is the new canvas width in "
"<glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>, and Y is the new height of "
"the canvas in <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>. "
"<userinput>canvassize</userinput> can be abbreviated to <userinput>cs</"
"userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>canvassize</userinput> आदेशेन भवान् कैनवासस्य आकारं सेट् कर्तुं शक्नोति । एतत् "
"X तथा Y निवेशरूपेण गृह्णाति, यत्र X <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">पिक्सेल</"
"glossterm> मध्ये नूतनं कैनवासविस्तारः अस्ति, Y च <glossterm linkend=\"pixels"
"\">पिक्सेलेषु< मध्ये कैनवासस्य नूतना ऊर्ध्वता अस्ति /ग्लोस्टर्म>। <userinput>canvassize</"
"userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>cs</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>canvascolor (cc)</term>"
msgstr "<term>canvascolor (cc)</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:326
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>canvascolor (cc)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>कैनवास्वर्ण (cc)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid "canvascolor R,G,B"
msgstr "canvascolor R,G,B"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:327
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> set the color of the canvas. "
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> takes an <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">RGB "
"combination</glossterm> as input. <userinput>canvascolor</userinput> can be "
"abbreviated to <userinput>cc</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> कैनवासस्य वर्णं सेट् कुर्वन्तु । "
"<userinput>canvascolor</userinput> एकं <glossterm linkend=\"rgb\">RGB संयोजनं</"
"glossterm> निवेशरूपेण गृह्णाति । <userinput>canvascolor</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं "
"<userinput>cc</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:334
#, no-c-format
msgid "Commands to clean up"
msgstr "स्वच्छतां कर्तुं आदेशाः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:335
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"There are two commands to clean up the canvas after you have made a mess."
msgstr "भवता गडबडं कृत्वा कैनवासस्य शोधनार्थं द्वौ आदेशौ स्तः ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>clear (ccl)</term>"
msgstr "<पद>स्पष्ट (ccl)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:339
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>clear (ccl)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>स्पष्ट (ccl)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid "clear"
msgstr "स्पष्टः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:340
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"With <userinput>clear</userinput> you can clean all drawings from the "
"canvas. All other things remain: the position and angle of the turtle, the "
"canvascolor, the visibility of the turtle, and the canvas size."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>clear</userinput> इत्यनेन भवान् कैनवासात् सर्वाणि रेखाचित्रं स्वच्छं कर्तुं "
"शक्नोति । अन्ये सर्वे अवशिष्टाः सन्ति : कच्छपस्य स्थितिः कोणः च, कैनवासरङ्गः, कच्छपस्य "
"दृश्यता, कैनवासस्य आकारः च ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>reset</term>"
msgstr "<term>reset</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:347
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>reset</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पुनर्स्थापन</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>reset</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>पुनः सेट्</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:348
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>reset</userinput> cleans much more thoroughly than the "
"<userinput>clear</userinput> command. After a <userinput>reset</userinput> "
"command everything is like is was when you had just started &kturtle;. The "
"turtle is positioned at the middle of the screen, the canvas color is white, "
"the turtle draws a black line on the canvas and the canvassize is set to 400 "
"x 400 pixels."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>reset</userinput> <userinput>clear</userinput> आदेशात् बहु अधिकं सम्यक् "
"स्वच्छं करोति । <userinput>reset</userinput> आदेशस्य अनन्तरं सर्वं is was इव अस्ति यदा "
"भवता &kturtle;. कच्छपः पटलस्य मध्ये स्थितः भवति, कैनवासस्य वर्णः श्वेतवर्णः भवति, कच्छपः "
"कैनवासस्य उपरि कृष्णरेखां आकर्षयति तथा च कैनवासस्य आकारः ४०० x ४०० पिक्सेल इति सेट् भवति"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:355
#, no-c-format
msgid "The turtle is a sprite"
msgstr "कच्छपः स्प्राइट् अस्ति"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:356
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First a brief explanation of what sprites are: sprites are small pictures "
"that can be moved around the screen, like we often see in computer games. "
"Our turtle is also a sprite. For more info see the glossary on <glossterm "
"linkend=\"sprites\">sprites</glossterm>."
msgstr ""
"प्रथमं स्प्राइट् किम् इति संक्षिप्तं व्याख्यानम् : स्प्राइट् इति लघुचित्रं यत् पटलस्य परितः "
"चालयितुं शक्यते, यथा वयं प्रायः सङ्गणकक्रीडासु पश्यामः । अस्माकं कच्छपः अपि स्प्राइट् अस्ति। "
"अधिकविवरणार्थं <glossterm linkend=\"sprites\">स्प्राइट्स्</glossterm> इत्यस्य शब्दकोशं "
"पश्यन्तु ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:357
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Next you will find a full overview on all commands to work with sprites."
msgstr ""
"तदनन्तरं स्प्राइट् इत्यनेन सह कार्यं कर्तुं सर्वेषां आदेशानां पूर्णं अवलोकनं भवन्तः प्राप्नुवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:358
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The current version of &kturtle; does not yet support the use of sprites "
"other than the turtle. With future versions you will be able to change the "
"turtle into something of your own design."
msgstr ""
"&kturtle इत्यस्य वर्तमानसंस्करणम्; अद्यापि कच्छपात् परं स्प्राइट्-प्रयोगं न समर्थयति । "
"भविष्यत्संस्करणैः सह भवन्तः कच्छपं स्वस्य डिजाइनस्य किमपि परिवर्तनं कर्तुं शक्नुवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>spriteshow (ss)</term>"
msgstr "<term>स्प्रिटशो (ss)</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:362
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>spriteshow (ss)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>स्प्रिटशो (स्स)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid "spriteshow"
msgstr "spriteshow इति"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:363
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>spriteshow</userinput> makes the turtle visible again after it "
"has been hidden. <userinput>spriteshow</userinput> can be abbreviated to "
"<userinput>ss</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>spriteshow</userinput> कच्छपं निगूढं कृत्वा पुनः दृश्यमानं करोति । "
"<userinput>spriteshow</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं <userinput>ss</userinput> इति "
"कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>spritehide (sh)</term>"
msgstr "<पद>स्प्रिटहिदे (श)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:370
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>spritehide (sh)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>स्प्रिटहिदे (श)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid "spritehide"
msgstr "spritehide इति"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:371
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>spritehide</userinput> hides the turtle. This can be used if the "
"turtle does not fit in your drawing. <userinput>spritehide</userinput> can "
"be abbreviated to <userinput>sh</userinput>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>spritehide</userinput> कच्छपं गोपयति । यदि कच्छपः भवतः रेखाचित्रे न "
"उपयुज्यते तर्हि एतत् उपयोक्तुं शक्यते । <userinput>spritehide</userinput> इति संक्षिप्तं "
"<userinput>sh</userinput> इति कर्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:378
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can the turtle write?"
msgstr "कच्छपः लिखितुं शक्नोति वा ?"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:379
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The answer is: <quote>yes</quote>. The turtle can write: it writes just "
"about everything you command it to."
msgstr ""
"उत्तरम्- <quote>आम्</quote> इति । कच्छपः लिखितुं शक्नोति: भवता आज्ञापितं सर्वं प्रायः "
"लिखति।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>print</term>"
msgstr "<पदं>मुद्रण</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:383
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>print</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>मुद्रण</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid "print X"
msgstr "print X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:384
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>print</userinput> command is used to command the turtle to "
"write something on the canvas. <userinput>print</userinput> takes numbers "
"and strings as input. You can <userinput>print</userinput> various numbers "
"and strings using the <quote>+</quote> symbol. See here a small example:"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>print</userinput> आदेशः कच्छपं कैनवासे किमपि लिखितुं आज्ञापयितुं उपयुज्यते । "
"<userinput>print</userinput> इत्यनेन सङ्ख्याः स्ट्रिंग् च इनपुट् रूपेण गृह्णाति । <quote>"
"+</quote> चिह्नस्य उपयोगेन भवान् <userinput>मुद्रणं</userinput> कर्तुं शक्नोति । अत्र लघु "
"उदाहरणं पश्यन्तु :"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:386
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$year = 2003\n"
"$author = \"Cies\"\n"
"print $author + \" started the KTurtle project in \" + $year + \" and still "
"enjoys working on it!\""
msgstr ""
"$वर्ष = २००३\n"
"$author = \"Cies\" ।\n"
"print $author + \" \" + $year + \" इत्यस्मिन् KTurtle परियोजना आरब्धवान् तथापि "
"तस्मिन् कार्यं कर्तुं आनन्दं प्राप्नोति!\""

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>fontsize</term>"
msgstr "<term>fontsize</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:393
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>fontsize</primary>"
msgstr "<primary>फॉन्ट् आकार</primary> इति"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid "fontsize X"
msgstr "fontsize X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:394
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>fontsize</userinput> sets the size of the font that is used by "
"<userinput>print</userinput>. <userinput>fontsize</userinput> takes one "
"input which should be a number. The size is set in <glossterm linkend="
"\"pixels\">pixels</glossterm>."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>fontsize</userinput> इत्यनेन <userinput>print</userinput> इत्यनेन "
"उपयुज्यमानस्य फन्ट् इत्यस्य आकारः सेट् भवति । <userinput>fontsize</userinput> एकं निवेशं "
"गृह्णाति यत् संख्या भवितुम् अर्हति । आकारः <glossterm linkend=\"pixels\">पिक्सेल</"
"glossterm> इत्यत्र सेट् भवति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:401
#, no-c-format
msgid "Mathematical commands"
msgstr "गणितीय आदेश"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:402
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The following commands are &kturtle;'s more advanced mathematical commands."
msgstr "निम्नलिखित आदेशाः &kturtle; इत्यस्य अधिक उन्नतगणितीय आदेशाः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>round</term>"
msgstr "<पदं>गोल</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:406
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>round</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>गोल</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid "round(x)"
msgstr "गोल(x)"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:407
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>round</userinput> the given number to the nearest integer. "
"<screen>\n"
"print round(10.8)\n"
"forward 20\n"
"print round(10.3)\n"
"</screen> With this code the turtle will print the numbers 11 and 10."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>round</userinput> दत्तां संख्यां समीपस्थं पूर्णाङ्कं प्रति । <स्क्रीन्>\n"
"मुद्रण गोल(१०.८) २.\n"
"अग्रे २०\n"
"मुद्रण गोल(१०.३) २.\n"
"</screen> एतेन कोडेन कच्छपः ११, १० च सङ्ख्याः मुद्रयिष्यति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>random (rnd)</term>"
msgstr "<पद>यादृच्छिक (रन्द)</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:416
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>random (rnd)</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>यादृच्छिक (रन्द)</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid "random X,Y"
msgstr "यादृच्छिक X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:417
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>random</userinput> is a command that takes input and gives "
"output. As input are required two numbers, the first (X) sets the minimum "
"output, the second (Y) sets the maximum. The output is a randomly chosen "
"number that is equal or greater than the minimum and equal or smaller than "
"the maximum. Here a small example: <screen>\n"
"repeat 500 {\n"
"  $x = random 1,20\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnleft 10 - $x\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Using the <userinput>random</userinput> command you can add a bit "
"of chaos to your program."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>random</userinput> इति आदेशः यः निवेशं गृहीत्वा निर्गमं ददाति । यथा इनपुट् "
"द्वौ सङ्ख्याः आवश्यकौ भवतः, प्रथमः (X) न्यूनतमं आउटपुट् सेट् करोति, द्वितीयः (Y) अधिकतमं "
"सेट् करोति । आउटपुट् यादृच्छिकरूपेण चयनिता संख्या भवति या न्यूनतमस्य समाना वा अधिका वा "
"अधिकतमस्य समाना वा लघु वा भवति । अत्र लघु उदाहरणम् : <screen>\n"
"पुनरावृत्ति ५०० { १.\n"
"  $x = यादृच्छिक 1,20\n"
"  अग्रे $x\n"
"  turnleft 10 - $x\n"
"} .\n"
"</screen> <userinput>random</userinput> आदेशस्य उपयोगेन भवान् स्वस्य कार्यक्रमे "
"किञ्चित् अराजकतां योजयितुं शक्नोति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>mod</term>"
msgstr "<पद>मोद</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:426
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>mod</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>मोद्</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid "mod X,Y"
msgstr "mod X,Y"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:427
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>mod</userinput> returns remainder of the division of first "
"number by the second number."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>mod</userinput> प्रथमसङ्ख्यायाः द्वितीयसङ्ख्यायाः विभागस्य अवशिष्टं "
"प्रत्यागच्छति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>sqrt</term>"
msgstr "<पद>स्कृट्</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:434
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>sqrt</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>स्कर्त्</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid "sqrt X"
msgstr "sqrt X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:435
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>sqrt</userinput> command is sued to find the square root of a "
"number, X."
msgstr "<userinput>sqrt</userinput> आदेशः सङ्ख्यायाः वर्गमूलं X अन्वेष्टुं मुकदमा क्रियते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>pi</term>"
msgstr "<पद>पि</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:452
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>pi</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पि</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>pi</screen>"
msgstr "<स्क्रीन्>पि</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:453
#, no-c-format
msgid "This command returns the constant Pi, <userinput>3.14159</userinput>."
msgstr "एषः आदेशः नित्यं Pi, <userinput>3.14159</userinput> इति प्रत्यागच्छति ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sin<indexterm><primary>sin</primary></indexterm>, "
"cos<indexterm><primary>cos</primary></indexterm>, tan"
msgstr ""
"पाप<indexterm><primary>sin</primary></indexterm>, को<indexterm><primary>cos</"
"primary></indexterm>, तन्"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:462
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>tan</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>तन</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"sin X\n"
"cos X\n"
"tan X"
msgstr ""
"विना X\n"
"कोस्\n"
"अतः X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:464
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These three commands represent the world famous trigoniometrical functions "
"<userinput>sin</userinput>, <userinput>cos</userinput> and <userinput>tan</"
"userinput>. The input argument of these commands, X, is a <link linkend="
"\"number\">number</link>."
msgstr ""
"एते त्रयः आदेशाः विश्वप्रसिद्धत्रिकोणमितीयकार्यं प्रतिनिधियन्ति<userinput> पापम्</"
"userinput> , ९.<userinput> कोस्</userinput> तथा<userinput> तन्</userinput> . "
"एतेषां आदेशानां निवेशतर्कः X इति a<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> ."

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"arcsin<indexterm><primary>arcsin</primary></indexterm>, "
"arccos<indexterm><primary>arccos</primary></indexterm>, arctan"
msgstr ""
"आर्कसिन्<indexterm><primary>arcsin</primary></indexterm>, "
"आर्कोस<indexterm><primary>arccos</primary></indexterm>, आर्कटान्"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:473
#, no-c-format
msgid "arctan"
msgstr "आर्कटन"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"arcsin X\n"
"arccos X\n"
"arctan X"
msgstr ""
"arcsin X\n"
"arcos X\n"
"आर्कटन X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:475
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"These commands are the inverse functions of <link linkend=\"sin\">sin</"
"link>, <link linkend=\"cos\">cos</link> and <link linkend=\"tan\">tan</"
"link>. The input argument of these commands, X, is a <link linkend=\"number"
"\">number</link>."
msgstr ""
"एते आदेशाः इत्यस्य विलोमकार्याणि सन्ति<link linkend=\"sin\"> पापम्</link> , ९.<link "
"linkend=\"cos\"> कोस्</link> तथा<link linkend=\"tan\"> तन्</link> . एतेषां "
"आदेशानां निवेशतर्कः X इति a<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> ."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:482
#, no-c-format
msgid "Input and feedback through dialogs"
msgstr "संवादद्वारा निवेशः प्रतिक्रिया च"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:483
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"A dialog is a small pop-up window that provides some feedback or asks for "
"some input. &kturtle; has two commands for dialogs, namely: "
"<userinput>message</userinput> and <userinput>ask</userinput>"
msgstr ""
"संवादः एकः लघुः पॉप-अप विण्डो अस्ति यः किञ्चित् प्रतिक्रियां ददाति अथवा किञ्चित् निवेशं "
"याचते । &kturtle; संवादस्य कृते द्वौ आदेशौ स्तः, यथा : <userinput>message</"
"userinput> तथा <userinput>ask</userinput>"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>message</term>"
msgstr "<पद>सन्देशः</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:487
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>message</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>सन्देश</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid "message X"
msgstr "सन्देशः X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:488
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>message</userinput> command takes a <link linkend=\"string"
"\">string</link> as input. It shows a pop-up dialog containing the text from "
"the <link linkend=\"string\">string</link>."
msgstr ""
"द<userinput> सन्देशः</userinput> आदेशः गृह्णाति क<link linkend=\"string\"> सूत्र</"
"link> निवेशरूपेण। इदं एकं pop-up संवादं दर्शयति यस्मिन् पाठः अस्ति<link linkend=\"string"
"\"> सूत्र</link> ."

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:490
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"message \"Cies started KTurtle in 2003 and still enjoys working on it!\""
msgstr ""
"message \"Cies इत्यनेन २००३ तमे वर्षे KTurtle इति संस्था आरब्धा, अद्यापि तस्मिन् कार्यं "
"कुर्वन् आनन्दं लभते!\""

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>ask</term>"
msgstr "<पद>पृच्छ</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:497
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>ask</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पृच्छ</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid "ask X"
msgstr "पृच्छतु X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:498
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>ask</userinput> takes a <link linkend=\"string\">string</link> as "
"input. It shows this string in a pop-up dialog (similar to <link linkend="
"\"message\">message</link>), along with an input field. After the user has "
"entered a <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> or a <link linkend=\"string"
"\">string</link> into this, the result can be stored in a <link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> or passed as an argument to a "
"<link linkend=\"commands\">command</link>. For example: <screen>\n"
"$in = ask \"What is your year of birth?\"\n"
"$out = 2003 - $in\n"
"print \"In 2003 you were \" + $out + \" years old at some point.\"\n"
"</screen> If the user cancels the input dialog, or does not enter anything "
"at all, the <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> is "
"empty."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>पृच्छतु</userinput> गृह्णाति क<link linkend=\"string\"> सूत्र</link> "
"निवेशरूपेण। एतत् स्ट्रिंग् एकस्मिन् pop-up संवादे (सदृशे) दर्शयति<link linkend=\"message\"> "
"सन्देशः</link> ), निवेशक्षेत्रेण सह । उपयोक्तुः प्रविष्टस्य अनन्तरं क<link linkend=\"number"
"\"> संख्या</link> अथवा क<link linkend=\"string\"> सूत्र</link> अस्मिन्, परिणामः "
"क<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चरः</link> वा तर्करूपेण पारितः "
"क<link linkend=\"commands\"> आदेश</link> . उदाहरणतया:<screen> $in = ask &quot;"
"भवतः जन्मवर्षं किम्?&quot; $out = 2003 - $in print &quot;२००३ तमे वर्षे भवान् "
"कस्मिन्चित् समये &quot; + $out + &quot; वर्षीयः आसीत्।&quot;</screen> यदि उपयोक्ता "
"निवेशसंवादं रद्दं करोति, अथवा किमपि सर्वथा न प्रविशति, तर्हि...<link linkend="
"\"assignment-of-variables\"> चरः</link> शून्यम् अस्ति।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:511
#, no-c-format
msgid "Assignment of variables"
msgstr "चरानाम् नियुक्तिः"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:512
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"First we have a look at variables, then we look at assigning values to those "
"variables."
msgstr "प्रथमं वयं चरानाम् अवलोकनं कुर्मः, ततः तेभ्यः चरानाम् मूल्यानि नियुक्तुं पश्यामः ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:516
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Variables are words that start with a <quote>$</quote>, in the <link linkend="
"\"the-editor\">editor</link> they are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> "
"with purple."
msgstr ""
"चराः क इत्यनेन आरभ्यमाणाः शब्दाः सन्ति<quote> $</quote> , इति<link linkend=\"the-"
"editor\"> सम्पादक</link> ते सन्ति<glossterm> प्रकाशितम्</glossterm> बैंगनीवर्णेन सह ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:518
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Variables can contain any <link linkend=\"number\">number</link>, <link "
"linkend=\"string\">string</link> or <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean "
"(true/false) value</link>. Using the assignment, <userinput>=</userinput>, a "
"variable is given its content. It will keep that content until the program "
"finishes executing or until the variable is reassigned to something else."
msgstr ""
"चरेषु कोऽपि भवितुं शक्नोति<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> , ९.<link linkend="
"\"string\"> सूत्र</link> वा<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> boolean (सत्य/असत्य) "
"मूल्यम्</link> . असाइनमेण्ट् इत्यस्य उपयोगेन, २.<userinput> =</userinput> , एकं चरं तस्य "
"सामग्रीं दीयते । यावत् प्रोग्राम् निष्पादनं समाप्तं न भवति तावत् यावत् अथवा यावत् चरः "
"अन्यस्मिन् किमपि प्रति पुनः नियुक्तः न भवति तावत् यावत् तत् सामग्रीं स्थापयिष्यति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:520
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"You can use variables, once assigned, just as if they are their content. For "
"instance in the following piece of &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$x = 10\n"
"$x = $x / 3\n"
"print $x\n"
"</screen> First the variable <userinput>$x</userinput> is assigned to "
"<userinput>10</userinput>. Then <userinput>$x</userinput> is reassigned to "
"itself divided by <userinput>3</userinput> &mdash; this effectively means "
"<userinput>$x</userinput> is reassigned to product of <userinput>10 / 3</"
"userinput>. Finally <userinput>$x</userinput> is printed. In line two and "
"three you see that <userinput>$x</userinput> is used as if it is its "
"contents."
msgstr ""
"भवन्तः चरानाम् उपयोगं कर्तुं शक्नुवन्ति, एकवारं नियुक्ताः, यथा ते तेषां सामग्रीः सन्ति । यथा "
"&turtlescript;: <screen> इत्यस्य निम्नलिखितखण्डे\n"
"$x = 10\n"
"$x = $x / 3\n"
"मुद्रणं $x\n"
"</screen> प्रथमं <userinput>$x</userinput> इति चरं <userinput>10</userinput> "
"इत्यत्र नियुक्तं भवति । ततः <userinput>$x</userinput> पुनः <userinput>3</"
"userinput> इत्यनेन विभक्तं स्वयमेव नियुक्तं भवति &mdash; अस्य प्रभावीरूपेण अर्थः अस्ति यत् "
"<userinput>$x</userinput> <userinput>10 / 3</userinput> इत्यस्य उत्पादे पुनः "
"नियुक्तम् अस्ति । अन्ते <userinput>$x</userinput> मुद्रितं भवति । द्वितीयत्रिपङ्क्तौ "
"भवन्तः पश्यन्ति यत् <userinput>$x</userinput> इत्यस्य उपयोगः तस्य सामग्री इव भवति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:524
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Variables have to be assigned in order to be used. For example: <screen>\n"
"print $n\n"
"</screen> Will result in an error message."
msgstr ""
"चरानाम् उपयोगाय नियुक्तिः कर्तव्या भवति । यथा - <screen>\n"
"print $n\n"
"</screen> त्रुटिसन्देशस्य परिणामः भविष्यति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:528
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Please consider the following piece of &turtlescript;: <screen>\n"
"$a = 2004\n"
"$b = 25\n"
"\n"
"# the next command prints \"2029\"\n"
"print $a + $b\n"
"backward 30\n"
"# the next command prints \"2004 plus 25 equals 2029\"\n"
"print $a + \" plus \" + $b + \" equals \" + ($a + $b)\n"
"</screen> In the first two lines the variables <userinput>$a</userinput> and "
"<userinput>$b</userinput> are set to 2004 and 25. Then in two "
"<userinput>print</userinput> commands with a <userinput>backward 30</"
"userinput> in between are executed. The comments before the "
"<userinput>print</userinput> commands explain what they are doing. The "
"command <userinput>backward 30</userinput> is there to make sure every "
"output is on a new line. As you see variables can be used just as if their "
"where what they contain, you can use them with any kind of <link linkend="
"\"operators\">operators</link> or give them as input when invoking <link "
"linkend=\"commands\">commands</link>."
msgstr ""
"कृपया &amp;turtlescript; इत्यस्य निम्नलिखितखण्डं विचारयन्तु।<screen> $a = 2004 $b = "
"25 # अग्रिमः आदेशः &quot;2029&quot; मुद्रयति print $a + $b backward 30 # अग्रिमः "
"आदेशः &quot;2004 plus 25 equals 2029&quot; print $a + &quot; plus &quot; + $b "
"+ &quot; equals &quot; मुद्रयति । + ($क + $ख) २.</screen> प्रथमपङ्क्तौ "
"चराः<userinput> $क</userinput> तथा<userinput> $ख</userinput> 2004 तथा 25 इति "
"सेट् भवन्ति ततः द्वयोः<userinput> मुद्रणम्</userinput> आदेशाः सह क<userinput> "
"पश्चात्तापः ३०</userinput> मध्ये निष्पाद्यन्ते । पूर्वं टिप्पण्यानि<userinput> मुद्रणम्</"
"userinput> आज्ञाः किं कुर्वन्ति इति व्याख्यायन्ते। आदेशः<userinput> पश्चात्तापः ३०</"
"userinput> प्रत्येकं आउटपुट् नूतनरेखायां भवति इति सुनिश्चितं कर्तुं तत्र अस्ति । यथा भवन्तः "
"पश्यन्ति चराः यथा तेषां where what they contain, इव उपयोक्तुं शक्यन्ते, भवन्तः तान् "
"किमपि प्रकारस्य सह उपयोक्तुं शक्नुवन्ति<link linkend=\"operators\"> संचालकाः</link> "
"अथवा आह्वानकाले तान् निवेशरूपेण ददातु<link linkend=\"commands\"> आदेशाः</link> ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:534
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"One more example: <screen>\n"
"$name = ask \"What is your name?\"\n"
"print \"Hi \" + $name + \"! Good luck while learning the art of "
"programming...\"\n"
"</screen> Pretty straight forward. Again you can see that the variable "
"<userinput>$name</userinput>, treated just like a string."
msgstr ""
"एकं उदाहरणम् अपि : <screen>\n"
"$name = ask \"भवतः नाम किम्?\"\n"
"print \"हाय \" + $name + \"! प्रोग्रामिंग् कलां शिक्षमाणः शुभकामना...\"\n"
"</screen> सुन्दरं ऋजुं अग्रे। पुनः भवन्तः द्रष्टुं शक्नुवन्ति यत् <userinput>$name</"
"userinput> इति चरं, स्ट्रिंग् इव व्यवहारः कृतः ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:538
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"When using variables the <link linkend=\"the-inspector\">inspector</link> is "
"very helpful. It shows you the contents of all variables that are currently "
"in use."
msgstr ""
"चरानाम् उपयोगं कुर्वन् the<link linkend=\"the-inspector\"> निरीक्षकः</link> अतीव "
"सहायकम् अस्ति। एतत् भवन्तं सर्वेषां चरानाम् सामग्रीं दर्शयति ये वर्तमानकाले प्रयुक्ताः सन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:544
#, no-c-format
msgid "Controlling execution"
msgstr "निष्पादनं नियन्त्रयन्"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:545
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The execution controllers enable you &mdash; as their name implies &mdash; "
"to control execution."
msgstr ""
"निष्पादननियन्त्रकाः भवन्तं सक्षमं कुर्वन्ति &mdash; यथा तेषां नाम सूचयति &mdash; निष्पादनं "
"नियन्त्रयितुं ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:546
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Execution controlling commands are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with "
"dark green in a bold font type. The brackets are mostly used together with "
"execution controllers and they are <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> with "
"black."
msgstr ""
"निष्पादननियन्त्रणादेशाः <glossterm>उद्घाटिताः</glossterm> इति गाढे फन्ट् प्रकारे "
"श्यामहरिद्रेण सह भवन्ति । कोष्ठकाः अधिकतया निष्पादननियन्त्रकैः सह उपयुज्यन्ते तथा च ते "
"कृष्णेन सह <glossterm>highlighted</glossterm> भवन्ति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:549
#, no-c-format
msgid "Have the turtle wait"
msgstr "कच्छपं प्रतीक्षतु"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:550
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"If you have done some programming in &kturtle; you have might noticed that "
"the turtle can be very quick at drawing. This command makes the turtle wait "
"for a given amount of time."
msgstr ""
"यदि भवान् &kturtle; भवता अवलोकितं स्यात् यत् कच्छपः आकर्षणे अतीव शीघ्रं भवितुम् अर्हति । "
"एतेन आदेशेन कच्छपः दत्तकालं प्रतीक्षते ।"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>wait</term>"
msgstr "<term>प्रतीक्षा</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:553
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>wait</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>प्रतीक्ष</primary>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid "wait X"
msgstr "प्रतीक्षा X"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:554
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>wait</userinput> makes the turtle wait for X seconds. <screen>\n"
"repeat 36 {\n"
"  forward 5\n"
"  turnright 10\n"
"  wait 0.5\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> This code draws a circle, but the turtle will wait half a second "
"after each step. This gives the impression of a slow-moving turtle."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>wait</userinput> कच्छपं X सेकण्ड् यावत् प्रतीक्षां करोति । <स्क्रीन्>\n"
"पुनरावृत्तिः ३६ { .\n"
"  अग्रे ५\n"
"  turnright 10\n"
"  प्रतीक्ष्यताम् 0.5\n"
"} .\n"
"</screen> एषः कोडः वृत्तं आकर्षयति, परन्तु कच्छपः प्रत्येकं पदे अर्धसेकेण्ड् प्रतीक्षते । अनेन "
"मन्दगतिना कच्छपस्य आभासः भवति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:564
#, no-c-format
msgid "Execute <quote>if</quote>"
msgstr "<quote>if</quote> इति निष्पादयन्तु"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>if</term>"
msgstr "<पद>यदि</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:567
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>if</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>यदि</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:568
#, no-c-format
msgid "if <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... }"
msgstr "यदि<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन इति</link> { ... } ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:568
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The code that is placed between the brackets will only be executed "
"<userinput>if</userinput> the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean value</"
"link> evaluates <quote>true</quote>. <screen>\n"
"$x = 6\n"
"if $x &gt; 5 {\n"
"  print \"$x is greater than five!\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> On the first line <userinput>$x</userinput> is set to 6. On the "
"second line a <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparing operator</"
"link> is used to evaluate <userinput>$x &gt; 5</userinput>. Since this "
"evaluates <quote>true</quote>, 6 is larger than 5, the execution controller "
"<userinput>if</userinput> will allow the code between the brackets to be "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"कोष्ठकानां मध्ये यः कोडः स्थापितः सः केवलं निष्पादितः भविष्यति<userinput> यदि</"
"userinput> the<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन मूल्य</link> मूल्याङ्कनं "
"करोति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> .<screen> $x = 6 if $x &gt; 5 { print &quot;$x "
"पञ्चभ्यः अधिकः अस्ति!&quot; } .</screen> प्रथमपङ्क्तौ<userinput> $x</userinput> is "
"set to 6. द्वितीयपङ्क्तौ a<link linkend=\"comparing-operators\"> तुलनां कुर्वन् "
"संचालकः</link> मूल्याङ्कनार्थं प्रयुज्यते<userinput> $x &gt; ५</userinput> . यतः एतेन "
"मूल्याङ्कनं भवति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> , ६ ५ इत्यस्मात् बृहत्तरः, "
"निष्पादननियन्त्रकः<userinput> यदि</userinput> कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडं निष्पादयितुं अनुमन्यते "
"।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:577
#, no-c-format
msgid "If not, in other words: <quote>else</quote>"
msgstr "यदि न, अन्येषु शब्देषु- <quote>अन्य</quote> इति"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>else</term>"
msgstr "<पद>अन्य</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:580
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>else</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>अन्य</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid "if <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... } else { ... }"
msgstr ""
"यदि<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन इति</link> { ... } उत { ... }"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:581
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>else</userinput> can be used in addition to the execution "
"controller <link linkend=\"if\"><userinput>if</userinput></link>. The code "
"between the brackets after <userinput>else</userinput> is only executed if "
"the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> evaluates <quote>false</"
"quote>. <screen>\n"
"reset\n"
"$x = 4\n"
"if $x &gt; 5 {\n"
"  print \"$x is greater than five!\"\n"
"} else {\n"
"  print \"$x is smaller than six!\"\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> The <link linkend=\"comparing-operators\">comparing operator</"
"link> evaluates the expression <userinput>$x &gt; 5</userinput>. Since 4 is "
"not greater than 5 the expression evaluates <quote>false</quote>. This means "
"the code between the brackets after <userinput>else</userinput> gets "
"executed."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>उत</userinput> निष्पादननियन्त्रकस्य अतिरिक्तं उपयोक्तुं शक्यते<link linkend="
"\"if\"><userinput> यदि</userinput></link> . पश्चात् कोष्ठकानां मध्ये "
"कोडः<userinput> उत</userinput> केवलं निष्पादितं भवति यदि द<link linkend="
"\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन इति</link> मूल्याङ्कनं करोति<quote> असत्य</quote> ."
"<screen> reset $x = 4 if $x &gt; 5 { print &quot;$x पञ्चभ्यः अधिकः अस्ति!"
"&quot; } else { print &quot;$x षड्भ्यः लघुः अस्ति!&quot; } .</screen> द<link "
"linkend=\"comparing-operators\"> तुलनां कुर्वन् संचालकः</link> व्यञ्जनस्य मूल्याङ्कनं "
"करोति<userinput> $x &gt; ५</userinput> . यतः ४ ५ इत्यस्मात् अधिकः नास्ति इति "
"व्यञ्जनं मूल्याङ्कयति<quote> असत्य</quote> . अस्य अर्थः अस्ति यत् पश्चात् कोष्ठकानां मध्ये "
"कोडः<userinput> उत</userinput> निष्पादितः भवति।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:590
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>while</quote> loop"
msgstr "<quote>while</quote> इति पाशः"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>while</term>"
msgstr "<पदं>तथा</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:593
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>while</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिकः>तथा</प्राथमिकः>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid "while <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> { ... }"
msgstr "यावद्‌<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन इति</link> { ... } ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:594
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The execution controller <userinput>while</userinput> is a lot like <link "
"linkend=\"if\"><userinput>if</userinput></link>. The difference is that "
"<userinput>while</userinput> keeps repeating (looping) the code between the "
"brackets until the <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link> evaluates "
"<quote>false</quote>. <screen>\n"
"$x = 1\n"
"while $x &lt; 5 {\n"
"  forward 10\n"
"  wait 1\n"
"  $x = $x + 1\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> On the first line <userinput>$x</userinput> is set to 1. On the "
"second line <userinput>$x &lt; 5</userinput> is evaluated. Since the answer "
"to this question is <quote>true</quote> the execution controller "
"<userinput>while</userinput> starts executing the code between the brackets "
"until the <userinput>$x &lt; 5</userinput> evaluates <quote>false</quote>. "
"In this case the code between the brackets will be executed 4 times, because "
"every time the fifth line is executed <userinput>$x</userinput> increases by "
"1."
msgstr ""
"निष्पादननियन्त्रकः<userinput> यावद्‌</userinput> इति बहु इव अस्ति<link linkend=\"if"
"\"><userinput> यदि</userinput></link> . भेदः इति<userinput> यावद्‌</userinput> "
"कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडं पुनरावृत्तिं (लूपं) करोति यावत्...<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> "
"बूलियन इति</link> मूल्याङ्कनं करोति<quote> असत्य</quote> .<screen> $x = 1 while $x "
"&lt; 5 { अग्रे 10 प्रतीक्षा 1 $x = $x + 1 } .</screen> प्रथमपङ्क्तौ<userinput> $x</"
"userinput> इति सेट् भवति 1. द्वितीयपङ्क्तौ<userinput> $x &lt; ५</userinput> "
"मूल्याङ्कितः भवति। यतः अस्य प्रश्नस्य उत्तरम् अस्ति<quote> सत्यम्‌</quote> "
"निष्पादननियन्त्रकः<userinput> यावद्‌</userinput> कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडं निष्पादयितुं आरभते "
"यावत्...<userinput> $x &lt; ५</userinput> मूल्याङ्कनं करोति<quote> असत्य</quote> . "
"अस्मिन् सन्दर्भे कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडः ४ वारं निष्पादितः भविष्यति, यतः प्रत्येकं पञ्चमपङ्क्तिः "
"निष्पादिता भवति<userinput> $x</userinput> वर्धते १ ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:603
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>repeat</quote> loop"
msgstr "<quote>पुनरावृत्ति</quote> पाशः"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>repeat</term>"
msgstr "<पदं>पुनरावृत्तिः</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:606
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>repeat</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>पुनः</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid "repeat <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> { ... }"
msgstr "परिहरन<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> { ... } ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:607
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The execution controller <userinput>repeat</userinput> is a lot like <link "
"linkend=\"while\"><userinput>while</userinput></link>. The difference is "
"that <userinput>repeat</userinput> keeps repeating (looping) the code "
"between the brackets for as many times as the given number."
msgstr ""
"निष्पादननियन्त्रकः<userinput> परिहरन</userinput> इति बहु इव अस्ति<link linkend="
"\"while\"><userinput> यावद्‌</userinput></link> . भेदः इति<userinput> परिहरन</"
"userinput> कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडं यावत्वारं दत्ता संख्यायाः पुनरावृत्तिं (लूपं) करोति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:614
#, no-c-format
msgid "The <quote>for</quote> loop, a counting loop"
msgstr "<quote>for</quote> पाशः, गणनापाशः"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>for</term>"
msgstr "<पदं>कृते</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>for</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिकः>कृते</प्राथमिकः>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>to</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>तः</प्रथम>म्"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:617
#, no-c-format
msgid "step"
msgstr "चरण"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"for <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> = <link "
"linkend=\"number\">number</link> to <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> "
"{ ... }"
msgstr ""
"कृते<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चरः</link> =<link linkend="
"\"number\"> संख्या</link> इत्यस्मै<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> { ... } ."

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:618
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"The <userinput>for</userinput> loop is a <quote>counting loop</quote>, &ie; "
"it keeps count for you. The first number sets the variable to the value in "
"the first loop. Every loop the number is increased until the second number "
"is reached. <screen>\n"
"for $x = 1 to 10 {\n"
"  print $x * 7\n"
"  forward 15\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Every time the code between the brackets is executed the "
"<userinput>$x</userinput> is increased by 1, until <userinput>$x</userinput> "
"reaches the value of 10. The code between the brackets prints the <userinput>"
"$x</userinput> multiplied by 7. After this program finishes its execution "
"you will see the times table of 7 on the canvas."
msgstr ""
"<userinput>for</userinput> पाशः <quote>गणनापाशः</quote> अस्ति, &ie; भवतः कृते "
"गणनां करोति। प्रथमा संख्या प्रथमे लूप् मध्ये मूल्ये चरं सेट् करोति । प्रत्येकं पाशं यावत् द्वितीया "
"संख्या न प्राप्यते तावत् संख्या वर्धते। <स्क्रीन्>\n"
"$x कृते = 1 तः 10 { .\n"
"  मुद्रण $x * 7\n"
"  अग्रे १५\n"
"} .\n"
"</screen> प्रत्येकं कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडः निष्पादितः भवति तदा <userinput>$x</"
"userinput> 1 इत्यनेन वर्धते, यावत् <userinput>$x</userinput> 10 इत्यस्य मूल्यं न "
"प्राप्नोति ।कोष्ठकानां मध्ये कोडः मुद्रयति the <userinput>$x</userinput> multiplied "
"by 7. अस्य प्रोग्रामस्य निष्पादनं समाप्तस्य अनन्तरं भवन्तः 7 इत्यस्य times table इत्यस्य "
"उपरि द्रक्ष्यन्ति कैनवासः ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:623
#, no-c-format
msgid "The default step size of a loop is 1, you can use an other value with"
msgstr ""
"लूप् इत्यस्य पूर्वनिर्धारितः चरणस्य आकारः 1 अस्ति, यस्य सह अन्यं मूल्यं उपयोक्तुं शक्नुवन्ति"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:625
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"for <link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\">variable</link> = <link "
"linkend=\"number\">number</link> to <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> "
"step <link linkend=\"number\">number</link> { ... }"
msgstr ""
"कृते<link linkend=\"assignment-of-variables\"> चरः</link> =<link linkend="
"\"number\"> संख्या</link> इत्यस्मै<link linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> चरण<link "
"linkend=\"number\"> संख्या</link> { ... } ."

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:631
#, no-c-format
msgid "Leave a loop"
msgstr "एकं पाशं त्यजतु"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>break</term>"
msgstr "<पद>विच्छेद</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:634
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>break</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>विच्छेद</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>break</screen>"
msgstr "<स्क्रीन्>भङ्ग</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:635
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Terminates the current loop immediately and transfers control to the "
"statement immediately following that loop."
msgstr ""
"वर्तमान लूप् तत्क्षणमेव समाप्तं करोति तथा च तस्य लूप् इत्यस्य तत्क्षणं अनुवर्तमानं स्टेट्मेण्ट् प्रति "
"नियन्त्रणं स्थानान्तरयति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:642
#, no-c-format
msgid "Stop executing your program"
msgstr "स्वस्य कार्यक्रमस्य निष्पादनं त्यजन्तु"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>exit</term>"
msgstr "<term>निर्गम</term> इति"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:645
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>exit</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>निर्गम</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "<screen>exit</screen>"
msgstr "<screen>निर्गम</screen>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:646
#, no-c-format
msgid "Finishes the execution of your program."
msgstr "भवतः कार्यक्रमस्य निष्पादनं समाप्तं करोति ।"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:653
#, no-c-format
msgid "Checking assertions at runtime"
msgstr "रनटाइम् इत्यत्र प्रतिपादनानां जाँचः"

#. Tag: term
#: programming-reference.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "<term>assert</term>"
msgstr "<पद>प्रतिपादन</term>"

#. Tag: primary
#: programming-reference.docbook:656
#, no-c-format
msgid "<primary>assert</primary>"
msgstr "<प्राथमिक>प्रतिपादन</प्रथम>"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "assert <link linkend=\"boolean-value\">boolean</link>"
msgstr "प्रतिपादयतु<link linkend=\"boolean-value\"> बूलियन इति</link>"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:657
#, no-c-format
msgid "Can be used to reason about program or input correctness."
msgstr "कार्यक्रमस्य अथवा निवेशस्य सम्यक्त्वस्य विषये तर्कार्थं उपयोक्तुं शक्यते ।"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:659
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"$in = ask \"What is your year of birth?\"\n"
"# the year must be positive\n"
"assert $in > 0"
msgstr ""
"$in = ask \"भवतः जन्मवर्षं किम्?\"\n"
"# वर्षं सकारात्मकं भवितुमर्हति\n"
"$in > 0 इति प्रतिपादयन्तु"

#. Tag: title
#: programming-reference.docbook:668
#, no-c-format
msgid "Create your own commands with <quote>learn</quote>"
msgstr "<quote>learn</quote> इत्यनेन स्वकीयान् आदेशान् रचयन्तु"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:669
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"<userinput>learn</userinput><indexterm><primary>learn</primary></indexterm> "
"is special as it is used to create your own commands. The commands you "
"create can take <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</glossterm> and "
"return <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">output</glossterm>. Let us take a "
"look at how a new command is created: <screen>\n"
"learn circle $x {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $x\n"
"    turnleft 10\n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> The new command is called <userinput>circle</userinput>. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> takes one <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">input</glossterm> argument, to set the size of the circle. "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> returns no <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">output</glossterm>. The <userinput>circle</userinput> command can now be "
"used like a normal command in the rest of the code. See this example:"
msgstr ""
"<userinput>learn</userinput><indexterm><primary>learn</primary></indexterm> "
"इति विशेषः यतः तस्य उपयोगः भवतः स्वस्य आदेशानां निर्माणार्थं भवति । भवता निर्मिताः "
"आदेशाः <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</glossterm> गृहीत्वा "
"<glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">output</glossterm> इति प्रेषयितुं शक्नुवन्ति । "
"नूतनः आदेशः कथं निर्मीयते इति अवलोकयामः : <screen>\n"
"शिक्षन्तु वृत्तं $x { .\n"
"  पुनरावृत्तिः ३६ { .\n"
"    अग्रे $x\n"
"    वामभागे 10\n"
"  } .\n"
"} .\n"
"</screen> नूतनः आदेशः <userinput>circle</userinput> इति उच्यते । "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> एकं <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</"
"glossterm> तर्कं गृह्णाति, वृत्तस्य आकारं सेट् कर्तुं । <userinput>वृत्त</userinput> कोऽपि "
"<glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">निर्गम</glossterm> न ददाति । "
"<userinput>circle</userinput> आदेशः इदानीं शेषसङ्केतेषु सामान्यादेशवत् उपयोक्तुं शक्यते । "
"एतत् उदाहरणं पश्यन्तु-"

#. Tag: screen
#: programming-reference.docbook:672
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"learn circle $X {\n"
"  repeat 36 {\n"
"    forward $X \n"
"    turnleft 10 \n"
"  }\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"go 200,200 \n"
"circle 20\n"
"\n"
"go 300,200 \n"
"circle 40"
msgstr ""
"शिक्षन्तु वृत्तं $X { .\n"
"  पुनरावृत्तिः ३६ { .\n"
"    अग्रे $X \n"
"    वामभागे 10 \n"
"  } .\n"
"} .\n"
"\n"
"गच्छन्तु २,००,२०० \n"
"वृत्तम् २०\n"
"\n"
"गच्छन्तु ३००,२०० \n"
"वृत्तम् ४०"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:674
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"In the next example, a command with a return<indexterm><primary>return</"
"primary></indexterm> value is created. <screen>\n"
"learn faculty $x {\n"
"  $r = 1\n"
"  for $i = 1 to $x {\n"
"    $r = $r * $i\n"
"  }\n"
"  return $r\n"
"}\n"
"\n"
"print faculty 5\n"
"</screen> In this example a new command called <userinput>faculty</"
"userinput> is created. If the input of this command is <userinput>5</"
"userinput> then the output is <userinput>5*4*3*2*1</userinput>. By using "
"<userinput>return</userinput> the <glossterm linkend=\"input-output"
"\">output</glossterm> value is specified and the execution is returned."
msgstr ""
"अग्रिमे उदाहरणे return<indexterm><primary>return</primary></indexterm> मूल्येन सह "
"आदेशः निर्मितः भवति । <स्क्रीन्>\n"
"संकाय शिक्षन्तु $x { .\n"
"  $र = १\n"
"  $i = 1 तः $x { 100 पर्यन्तम् ।\n"
"    $र = $र * $i\n"
"  } .\n"
"  return $r\n"
"} .\n"
"\n"
"मुद्रण संकाय 5\n"
"</screen> अस्मिन् उदाहरणे <userinput>faculty</userinput> इति नूतनः आदेशः निर्मितः "
"अस्ति । यदि अस्य आदेशस्य निवेशः <userinput>5</userinput> अस्ति तर्हि निर्गमः "
"<userinput>5*4*3*2*1</userinput> अस्ति । <userinput>return</userinput> इत्यस्य "
"उपयोगेन <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">output</glossterm> मूल्यं निर्दिष्टं "
"भवति, निष्पादनं च प्रत्यागच्छति ।"

#. Tag: para
#: programming-reference.docbook:677
#, no-c-format
msgid ""
"Commands can have more than one <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</"
"glossterm>. In the next example, a command that draws a rectangle is "
"created: <screen>\n"
"learn box $x, $y {\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  forward $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"}\n"
"</screen> Now you can run <userinput>box 50, 100</userinput> and the turtle "
"will draw a rectangle on the canvas."
msgstr ""
"आदेशानां एकादशाधिकं <glossterm linkend=\"input-output\">input</glossterm> भवितुम् "
"अर्हति । अग्रिमे उदाहरणे आयतं आकर्षयति इति आदेशः निर्मितः भवति : <screen>\n"
"शिक्षन्तु पेटी $x, $y { .\n"
"  अग्रे $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  अग्रे $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  अग्रे $y\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"  अग्रे $x\n"
"  turnright 90\n"
"} .\n"
"</screen> इदानीं भवान् <userinput>box 50, 100</userinput> चालयितुं शक्नोति ततः "
"कच्छपः कैनवासस्य उपरि आयतं आकर्षयिष्यति ।"
